I am trying to build a rule-based engine, which can facilitate getting your 
coding tasks done with far less tokens than the normal.

Today's models are getting smarter and smarter where you can get done lot with 
shorter context as well. It doesn't need to be spoonfed with every granular detail 
to get the task finished.

The whole flow of this project is to map the existing code block tokens to a 
compressed token space, give it as context to the model, get the job done with fewer
tokens and map back the changes to the original code space in your local machine.

You are offloading the compute to your local machine at pre and post model interactions, leveraging the idle-laid CPU power of your local machine, rather depending completely on the remote resources. This can be a good
cost saver for the businesses, since there is a wider adoption of such models.
